  "text": "The result (29) has the following important consequence. Whatever the complete set of counterterms for the full space of ASch 5 solutions is, upon substituting the solutions (1) to (3), the counterterms must cancel the divergences coming from the right hand side of [CITATION_1] . This means that counterterms that contribute to the on-shell action divergently must equal, upon use of (1) to (3), the counterterms of the usual AAdS 5 action [23]",
